Greetings from the Career Development Team.

In view of the amazing response to our resume building and review sessions,
we resume the Career Connect series with a new set of events.

Interviews and Group Discussions (GDs) are a part of many companies who
visit the institute during placement season for student recruitment. Fret
not, if you are worried or feeling a lack of confidence.

In view of this, we are conducting a session on "Do's & Dont's for Group
discussions & Interviews" by Mr Ramnath Kanakadandi, an expert in this
field.

Date: 21/9/16(Wednesday)
Venue: DOMS 101
Time: 6:30 pm

For any queries contact:
Murali : +919176484686 <%2B919176484686

Speaker Bio: Ramnath Kanakadandi is a Mechanical Engineer from JNTU
Hyderabad and is an MBA from IIM Ahmedabad. He has worked for over 7 years
in the services sector in varied roles like Design, Operations, Six Sigma
etc., after which he has been mentoring and helping students to crack the
CAT, for the last 7 years. He is currently the National Course Director for
CAT, Study Abroad and UG courses with T.I.M.E and is based in Hyderabad. He
is a keen follower of Cricket and Tennis and is a big fan of MS Dhoni and
Rafael Nadal.

Regards,
Career Development Team

